\f0\fs48 \cf0 \'95 The NEMO Portal is designed to support \b \cf2 ontological (knowledge-based) classification \b0 \cf0 of ERP patterns and storage and retrieval of ERP data within a knowledge-based framework.\ \ \'95 Data are represented in \b \cf2 Resource Data Format (RDF) \b0 \cf0 , which are automatically generated by the \b \cf2 NEMO analysis workflow \b0 \cf0 . RDF files are then parsed, processed, and displayed in the Portal. \ \ \'95 Pattern classification is now performed within the Portal. Previously, we performed the classification (inferences) in Prot\'e9g\'e9 and then uploaded results to the Portal as a separate step. The Portal now runs inside a \b \cf2 Java Virtual Machine \b0 \cf0 , which allows direct integration with the \b \cf2 OWLAPI \b0 \cf0 . Thus, data are now classified and labeled automatically when users upload RDF files. \ \ \'95 The graphical interface makes it easy to \b \cf2 query and retrieve labeled patterns \b0 \cf0 from different datasets and to display their corresponding waveforms and topographic maps. This means that we can now process and view multiple datasets using an integrated, online application. This represents a major step towards our goal of providing support for \b \cf2 high-quality meta-analysis of ERP data \b0 \cf0 .\ }
